 Hampshire]]: [[John H. Sununu]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (until January 4), [[Judd Gregg]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (starting January 4)\n* [[Governor of New Jersey]]: [[Thomas Kean]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of New Mexico]]: [[Garrey Carruthers]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of New York]]: [[Mario Cuomo]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of North Carolina]]: [[James G. Martin]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of North Dakota]]: [[George A. Sinner]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Ohio]]: [[Dick Celeste]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Oklahoma]]: [[Henry Bellmon]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Oregon]]: [[Neil Goldschmidt]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Pennsylvania]]: [[Robert P. Casey]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Rhode Island]]: [[Edward D. DiPrete]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of South Carolina]]: [[Carroll A. Campbell, Jr.]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of South Dakota]]: [[George S. Mickelson]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Tennessee]]: [[Ned McWherter]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Texas]]: [[Bill Clements]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Utah]]: [[Norman H. Bangerter]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Vermont]]: [[Madeleine M. Kunin]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Virginia]]: [[Gerald L. Baliles]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Washington]]: [[Booth Gardner]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of West Virginia]]: [[Arch A. Moore, Jr.]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (until January 16), [[Gaston Caperton]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) (starting January 16)\n* [[Governor of Wisconsin]]: [[Tommy Thompson]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Wyoming]]: [[Mike Sullivan (governor)|Mike Sullivan]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]])\n}}\n\n=== Lieutenant governors ===\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Alabama]]: [[Jim Folsom, Jr.]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Alaska]]: [[Stephen McAlpine]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Arkansas]]: [[Winston Bryant]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Lieutenant Governor of California]]: [[Leo T. McCarthy]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]])\n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Colorado]]: [[Mike Callihan]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Connecticut]]: [[Joseph J. Fauliso]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Delaware]]: [[Shien Biau Woo]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) (until January 20), [[Dale E. Wolf]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (starting January 20)\n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Florida]]: [[Bobby Brantley]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Georgia]]: [[Zell Miller]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Hawaii]]: [[Ben Cayetano]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Idaho]]: [[Butch Otter]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Illinois]]: [[George H. Ryan]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Indiana]]: [[John Mutz]] ([