/18/covid-19-reserve-bank-reduce-overnight-policy-rate/|archive-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Tourism in Fiji|Tourism Fiji]] says consumer confidence in travel is currently really low.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fijivillage.com/news/Consumer-confidence-in-travel-is-currently-really-low---Tourism-Fiji-r58f4x/|title=Consumer confidence in travel is currently really low - Tourism Fiji|last=Fijivillage|website=www.fijivillage.com|language=en|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320192804/https://www.fijivillage.com/news/Consumer-confidence-in-travel-is-currently-really-low---Tourism-Fiji-r58f4x/|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* Reserve Bank of Fiji forecast the domestic economy to fall into a recession after almost a decade of economic growth.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fijitimes.com/fijis-central-bank-forecasts-recession-in-domestic-economy/ |title=Fiji\u2019s central bank forecasts recession in domestic economy |website=The Fiji Times |access-date=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n* The [[Fiji Indian organisations|TISI Sangam Convention]] had cancelled the 2020 annual event.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fijivillage.com/news/TISI-Sangam-cancels-2020-Annual-TISI-Sangam-Convention-due-to-COVID-19-845fxr/ |title=TISI Sangam cancels 2020 Annual TISI Sangam Convention due to COVID-19 |website=www.fijivillage.com |access-date=21 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321024332/https://www.fijivillage.com/news/TISI-Sangam-cancels-2020-Annual-TISI-Sangam-Convention-due-to-COVID-19-845fxr/ |archive-date=21 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* [[Fiji Football Association|Fiji Football]] had postponed all its scheduled matches, meetings and workshops.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fijitimes.com/fiji-fa-calls-off-matches-events/|title=Fiji FA calls off matches, events|website=The Fiji Times|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322061146/https://www.fijitimes.com/fiji-fa-calls-off-matches-events/|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*Construction Industry seeing a downturn where raw materials are running out.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fbcnews.com.fj/news/covid-19/construction-industry-seeing-a-downturn-due-to-covid-19/|title=Construction Industry seeing a downturn due to COVID-19|website=Fiji Broadcasting Corporation|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n*Nurses facing unprecedented physical and psychological challenges.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fbcnews.com.fj/news/covid-19/nurses-can-face-unprecedented-mental-challenges/|title=Nurses can face unprecedented mental challenges|website=Fiji Broadcasting Corporation|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in Fiji|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Fiji]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Oceania|Fiji]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Fiji]]\n", "name_user": "Keith D", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eApril 2020:Remove leading zero from dates", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Fiji"}
